==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sponsion
<hw>Spon"sion</hw> <pr>(-sh⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sponsio</ets>, fr. <ets>spondere</ets>, <ets>sponsum</ets>, to
promise solemnly.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of becoming surety for
another.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Internat. Law)</fld> <def>An act or engagement on
behalf of a state, by an agent not specially authorized for the purpose,
or by one who exceeds the limits of authority.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sponsional</ent>⟦br⟧
